title: I'm Just a Girl Who Can't Say D'oh
plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.
episode_title: I'm Just a Girl Who Can't Say D'oh

title: Simpsons Roasting on an Open Fire
plot: The family is forced to spend all of their savings to get Bart's new tattooo removed, and with no money for Christmas, Homer is forced to become a store Santa.
episode_title: Simpsons Roasting on an Open Fire

title: Bart the Genius
plot: Bart ends up at a school for gifted children after cheating on an IQ test.

title: Homer's Odyssey
plot: After losing his job, Homer contemplates ending it all, until he discovers a new life path as a safety advocate.

title: There's No Disgrace Like Home
plot: After being embarrassed by the rest of the family at a company picnic, Homer becomes obsessed with improving their behavior towards each other.

title: Bart the General
plot: After being beaten up by Nelson Muntz one too many times, Bart turns to Grampa for help, and soon leads a rebellion against the school bully.

title: Moaning Lisa
plot: A depressed Lisa's spirit is lifted when she meets a jazz-man, Bleeding Gums Murphy.

title: The Call of the Simpsons
plot: Homer takes the family camping, but it soon becomes a misadventure when they lose their equipment and Homer is mistaken for Bigfoot.

title: The Telltale Head
plot: Bart gets more than he bargained for when he saws the head off a statue of the town's founder.

title: Life on the Fast Lane
plot: Marge contemplates an affair with a handsome bowling instructor.

title: Homer's Night Out
plot: After a photograph of Homer canoodling with an exotic dancer is distributed throughout Springfield, he finds himself kicked out of the house by Marge.

title: The Crepes of Wrath
plot: Bart is sent to France on a student exchange program, where he's treated like a slave; An Albanian student takes Bart's place in the family.

title: Krusty Gets Busted
plot: Homer witnesses a robbery at the Kwik-E-Mart, where the culprit is a man dressed like Bart's hero, Krusty the Clown. But there's more than meets the eye?

title: Some Enchanted Evening
plot: Homer and Marge enjoy a night on the town, leaving the kids with a diabolical babysitter, with a surprising secret.

title: Bart Gets an F
plot: Mrs. Krabappel, fed up with Bart's lackadaisical approach to his studies, gives him an ultimatum: shape up or repeat the fourth grade.

title: Simpson and Delilah
plot: Homer lies on a medical insurance form in order to obtain a miracle hair restoring drug.

title: Treehouse of Horror
plot: The Simpsons move into a cursed house, then are abducted by aliens, before Homer is ensconced in a tale by Edgar Allen Poe.

title: Two Cars in Every Garage and Three Eyes on Every Fish
plot: After the power plant experiences bad publicity and is threatened with closure, Mr. Burns decides to run for Governor in order to have power over the law.
episode_title: Two Cars in Every Garage and Three Eyes on Every Fish

title: Dancin' Homer
plot: Homer's heckling of the Springfield Isotopes baseball team during one of their games inadvertently leads to his appointment as the new team mascot.

title: Dead Putting Society
plot: In an attempt to show up Ned Flanders, Homer pits Bart against Ned's son, Todd, in a miniature golf competition.

title: Bart vs. Thanksgiving
plot: On Thanksgiving, Bart gets into a fight with the family and runs away from home, before sharing a turkey dinner with a group of homeless people at a soup kitchen, and learning the true meaning of the holiday in the process.

title: Bart the Daredevil
plot: After seeing a motorcycle daredevil at a monster truck show, Bart becomes a death-defying daredevil skateboarder.

title: Itchy and Scratchy and Marge
plot: Marge becomes a crusader against cartoon violence after watching The Itchy and Scratchy Show.

title: Bart Gets Hit by a Car
plot: While skateboarding down the street, Bart is hit by a car driven by Mr. Burns. Homer turns down Mr. Burns' token offer of $100, and instead hires ambulance-chaser Lionel Hutz to bring an outrageous lawsuit against the millionaire.
episode_title: Bart Gets Hit by a Car

title: One Fish, Two Fish, Blowfish, Blue Fish
plot: After apparently consuming poison blowfish, Homer is told that he only has 24 hours to live.
episode_title: One Fish, Two Fish, Blowfish, Blue Fish

title: The Way We Was
plot: Homer and Marge tell the story of how they met and fell in love in high school.

title: Homer vs. Lisa and the 8th Commandment
plot: Homer gets a crooked cable guy to install free cable in the Simpson home, and as a result, Lisa faces an ethical crisis over her family's stealing.
episode_title: Homer vs. Lisa and the 8th Commandment

title: Principal Charming
plot: After attending a co-worker's wedding, Selma begins to fear she will die alone. However, when Homer tries to set her up with Principal Skinner, he falls for Patty instead.

title: Oh Brother, Where Art Thou?
plot: After Grampa is hospitalized, he reveals that Homer has a half-brother, and the family soon discovers the brother, named Herb, owns a car company. However Herb's hiring of Homer to design a new car may be his undoing.

title: Bart's Dog Gets an F
plot: After an uncontrollable Santa's Little Helper destroys several important Simpson possessions, Homer announces that he will be thrown out of the house unless he completes obedience training.

title: Old Money
plot: After Grampa's new girlfriend dies and leaves him $106,000 in her will, he tries to decide what to do with it.

title: Brush with Greatness
plot: After becoming trapped in a water slide, Homer decides to go on a diet, while Marge enrolls in an art class and is soon commissioned to paint a portrait of Mr. Burns.

title: Lisa's Substitute
plot: Lisa has a crush on her substitute teacher; Bart decides to run for class president.

title: The War of the Simpsons
plot: Homer must decide which is more important: completing counseling to save his marriage or skipping out to catch a legendary catfish. Meanwhile, at home, Bart and Lisa take advantage of Grampa's ignorance of the house rules.

title: Three Men and a Comic Book
plot: Bart, Milhouse and Martin each pitch in to buy an expensive comic book, which soon has a disastrous effect on their friendship.
episode_title: Three Men and a Comic Book

title: Blood Feud
plot: Bart saves Mr. Burns's life. But Homer becomes enraged when Mr. Burns doesn't return the favor by sending the Simpsons what he considers to be an appropriate "thank you" gift.

title: Stark Raving Dad
plot: Homer accidentally lands in a mental hospital and ends up sharing a room with a white man who thinks he is Michael Jackson.

title: Mr. Lisa Goes to Washington
plot: After winning a political essay contest, Lisa is invited to Washington, D.C., but she soon becomes upset after discovering how policy-making really works.

title: When Flanders Failed
plot: After wishing for Flanders to lose his business, Homer discovers that his neighbor is actually about to go bankrupt and decides to help him out.

title: Bart the Murderer
plot: After having a horrible day, Bart gets a job tending bar for a group of gangsters and becomes the prime suspect when Principal Skinner mysteriously disappears.

title: Homer Defined
plot: Homer is a hero after averting a nuclear meltdown that he nearly caused, but he doesn't want to tell anyone that he stopped it completely by accident.

title: Like Father, Like Clown
plot: Bart and Lisa try to reunite Krusty the Clown with his father.

title: Treehouse of Horror II
plot: The Simpson family receives a severed monkey's paw which can grant wishes, Bart gains magical powers which he uses to turn Homer into a Jack-in-the-box, and Mr. Burns uses Homer's brain to create a robot.

title: Lisa's Pony
plot: After ruining Lisa's performance at the school talent show, Homer tries to make it up by buying her a pony.

title: Saturdays of Thunder
plot: After Homer fails a fathering test, he decides to help Bart build his Soap Box Derby racer.

title: Flaming Moe's
plot: Moe claims that a drink that Homer invented is his own. After the drink makes the bar a local hot spot, Moe gains a number of fair-weather friends but loses Homer's friendship.

title: Burns Verkaufen der Kraftwerk
plot: Burns decides to retire and sells the power plant to a German consortium for an exorbitant price. Homer's laziness and inefficiency are quickly exposed by his new bosses, and he is laid off.

title: I Married Marge
plot: As Marge goes to the doctor for a pregnancy test, Homer tells the children of the events leading up to his marriage, and Bart's birth.

title: Radio Bart
plot: After Bart receives a microphone which can transmit through radios, he decides to pull a series of pranks and eventually convinces the town that a boy has fallen down a well.

title: Lisa the Greek
plot: Homer uses Lisa (and her prognostic skills) to help him bet on football games.

title: Homer Alone
plot: While Marge spends a couple of days at Rancho Relaxo after she has a breakdown, Bart and Lisa stay with Patty and Selma, and Homer stays at home to take care of Maggie.

title: Bart the Lover
plot: After Mrs. Krabappel gives Bart a month of detention, he gets his revenge by responding to her newspaper singles ad. Meanwhile, Marge suggests Homer to start a swear jar to stop him cursing.

title: Homer at the Bat
plot: Homer and his co-workers qualify for the plant softball team's league final, but Mr. Burns hires nine professional MLB players in order to win a $1 million bet.

title: Separate Vocations
plot: The results of a standardized test steer Bart in the direction of law and order at Springfield Elementary School. However, Lisa becomes so depressed by her results that she turns to juvenile delinquency.

title: Dog of Death
plot: The Simpsons wind up regretting paying for an expensive surgery for Santa's Little Helper. He then runs away from home, winds up in the animal shelter, and is adopted by Mr. Burns to become an attack dog.

title: Colonel Homer
plot: Homer becomes the manager of a beautiful young country singer and finds himself almost attracted to her, sparking Marge's jealousy.

title: Black Widower
plot: Sideshow Bob gets out of jail and plots to take his revenge on Bart by marrying his Aunt Selma and killing her.

title: The Otto Show
plot: After Otto loses his job as school bus driver because he does not have a license, Bart convinces Homer and Marge to let Otto stay with them until he gets back on his feet.

title: Bart's Friend Falls in Love
plot: Milhouse falls in love with Samantha, a new transfer student, and Bart becomes jealous of all the time they are spending together. Meanwhile, Homer orders a subliminal weight loss tape, but is given a vocabulary builder by mistake.

title: Brother, Can You Spare Two Dimes?
plot: After Homer "wins" a $2000 settlement with the plant for radiation affecting his sperm count, his brother Herb comes to Springfield with an idea that could help him get his fortune back.
episode_title: Brother, Can You Spare Two Dimes?

title: Kamp Krusty
plot: Bart and Lisa attend "Kamp Krusty" but it is nothing like they thought it would be; Homer's hair grows back and he loses weight while the kids are away.

title: A Streetcar Named Marge
plot: Marge stars in a musical adaptation of A Streetcar Named Desire on stage and is angry at Homer's lack of interest. Maggie leads a team of babies in regaining their pacifiers from Ayn Rand School For Tots.

title: Homer the Heretic
plot: After skipping church one week, Homer decides that he is never going back. However, when a calamity occurs, it takes the combined efforts of a number of people from different faiths to save him.

title: Lisa the Beauty Queen
plot: Lisa enters the Little Miss Springfield pageant.

title: Treehouse of Horror III
plot: An evil Krusty the Clown doll makes life hell for the Simpsons, Marge is captured by a giant ape who falls in love with her, and Bart inadvertently raises the dead.

title: Itchy & Scratchy: The Movie
plot: With Bart continually getting in trouble, Homer bans him from seeing the new Itchy & Scratchy movie.

title: Marge Gets a Job
plot: Marge takes a job at the nuclear plant to help pay for the house's foundation repair, and Mr. Burns is smitten by her.

title: New Kid on the Block
plot: Bart becomes infatuated with his new neighbor but she is more interested in someone else; Homer is kicked out of a restaurant after eating too much.

title: Mr. Plow
plot: Homer opens a snow plow business only to have his best friend Barney open a rival outfit, with commercials by Linda Ronstadt. Homer sends Barney into an avalanche, then feels guilty and saves his life.

title: Lisa's First Word
plot: While trying to coax Maggie into saying her first word, Homer and Marge talk about how Lisa spoke hers.

title: Homer's Triple Bypass
plot: Years of poor eating habits catch up with Homer when he suffers a massive heart attack. The family can't afford the triple bypass operation he needs from Dr. Hibbert, so they go to a discount quack named Nick Riviera.

title: Marge vs. the Monorail
plot: After receiving a considerable donation of money, Springfield builds a monorail system with Homer as the conductor, unaware they've just boarded a one-way train to Hell.

title: Selma's Choice
plot: Selma starts to feel broody, but after taking Bart and Lisa to Duff Gardens, she changes her mind.

title: Brother from the Same Planet
plot: When Bart gets tired of Hole: horrible parenting skills, he enrolled in the "Bigger Brother" program where he's assigned a fantastic role model.

title: I Love Lisa
plot: Feeling sorry for Ralph, Lisa sends him a Valentine card. Having developed a crush on her, Ralph invites Lisa to go see the Krusty the Clown show. She accepts but after Krusty asks them if they are boyfriend and girlfriend, Lisa lets Ralph know that she just wants them to be friends.

title: Duffless
plot: After Homer is arrested for DUI, and loses his driver's license, he is put to the ultimate test when Marge pressures him to give up beer for a month.

title: Last Exit to Springfield
plot: Homer becomes union leader and leads a company strike when Mr. Burns takes away the company dental plan.

title: So It's Come to This: A Simpsons Clip Show
plot: Bart's April fools prank results in a huge explosion that seriously injures the Simpsons patriarch.
episode_title: So It's Come to This: A Simpsons Clip Show

title: The Front
plot: Bart and Lisa decide to write their own episodes of the "Itchy and Scratchy" show after they begin to grow bored with the current scripts.

title: Whacking Day
plot: Marge attempts to home school Bart after he is expelled from Springfield Elementary. Meanwhile, Lisa protests a barbaric local holiday centered around clubbing snakes to death.

title: Marge in Chains
plot: A misunderstanding leads to Marge being imprisoned for shoplifting. In her absence, the family, and eventually, the town itself, descend into chaos.

title: Krusty Gets Kancelled
plot: A massive advertising blitz announces the arrival of something named "Gabbo". Eventually, Gabbo is revealed to be a Howdy Doody-esque dummy, whose sensational success causes Krusty the Clown's show to be canceled.

title: Homer's Barbershop Quartet
plot: After the kids find a record with Homer's picture on it, he recalls the story of how he achieved fame in the 1980s with his barbershop quartet, The Be Sharps.

title: Cape Feare
plot: After being released from prison on parole, Sideshow Bob plots to murder Bart.

title: Homer Goes to College
plot: When a surprise inspection of the nuclear power plant reveals that Homer is not qualified to do his job, he is forced to go to college.

title: Rosebud
plot: After his birthday party goes wrong, Mr. Burns begins to want his childhood toy, a teddy bear named Bobo; Homer finds that Maggie is in possession of the doll.

title: Treehouse of Horror IV
plot: Homer sells his soul to the Devil for a donut, Bart contends with a gremlin on the side of the school bus which only he can see, and the family discovers that Mr. Burns is a vampire.

title: Marge on the Lam
plot: A girls' night out turns into a high speed chase when Marge learns her friend is driving a stolen car.

title: Bart's Inner Child
plot: Brad Goodman, a self-help guru, comes to Springfield and identifies Bart as a role model for personal happiness because he is in touch with his inner child. Soon, the entire town begins to behave like him.

title: Boy Scoutz 'n the Hood
plot: After joining the Junior Campers while on a sugar high, Bart reluctantly invites Homer to accompany him on the group's annual father-son rafting trip, which soon goes awry.

title: The Last Temptation of Homer
plot: Homer's marriage is in trouble when he develops an attraction to a new co-worker.

title: $pringfield (Or, How I Learned to Stop Worrying and Love Legalized Gambling)
plot: In order to revitalize its economy, Springfield decides to legalize gambling. As a consequence, Marge becomes addicted to using slot machines, while Mr. Burns develops a Howard Hughes complex.
episode_title: $pringfield (Or, How I Learned to Stop Worrying and Love Legalized Gambling)

title: Homer the Vigilante
plot: An outbreak of burglaries inspires Homer to lead a vigilante group.

title: Bart Gets Famous
plot: Bart becomes an overnight sensation as the "I didn't do it" boy on Krusty the Clown's show.

title: Homer and Apu
plot: When Homer becomes ill after eating contaminated food bought at the Kwik-E-Mart, Apu is fired from his job.

title: Lisa vs. Malibu Stacy
plot: Lisa leads a protest against a talking doll which she believes is sexist.

title: Deep Space Homer
plot: In an effort to increase the dismal television ratings for their space launches, NASA decides to send an ordinary man into space, and Homer is chosen for the task.

title: Homer Loves Flanders
plot: After Flanders invites Homer to a football game, the pair become friends, but Homer's possessiveness and loutish behaviour slowly turns Ned against him.

title: Bart Gets an Elephant
plot: After Bart receives an elephant as a prize for calling in to a radio station, the animal proves to be too costly to care for and Homer decides to sell it.

title: Burns' Heir
plot: After coming close to death, Mr. Burns decides than it's time to find an heir to his empire, and chooses Bart because of his truly devious nature.

title: Sweet Seymour Skinner's Baadasssss Song
plot: Bart brings Santa's Little Helper to school with him on inspection day and gets Skinner fired, Bart is pleased until Ned Flanders is made his replacement.

title: The Boy Who Knew Too Much
plot: After playing truant from school, Bart witnesses the alleged assault of a waiter by Mayor Quimby's nephew, Freddy. However, if he comes forward, he will have to admit he skipped class, and face the consequences.
episode_title: The Boy Who Knew Too Much

title: Lady Bouvier's Lover
plot: Grampa falls in love with Marge's mother, but must compete with Mr. Burns for her heart.

title: Secrets of a Successful Marriage
plot: Homer begins teaching a class on how to have a successful marriage, but jeopardizes his own marriage by revealing secrets about himself and Marge.

title: Bart of Darkness
plot: After he breaks his leg and becomes confined to his room, Bart begins spying on the residents of Springfield with a telescope, and suspects Ned of murdering his wife.

title: Lisa's Rival
plot: Lisa is jealous when a new girl in class is smarter than she is. Meanwhile, Homer obtains a massive amount of sugar.

title: Another Simpsons Clip Show
plot: The family recalls past tales of lost love.

title: Itchy & Scratchy Land
plot: A family vacation to Itchy & Scratchy Land turns disastrous when the robots malfunction and turn on the tourists.

title: Sideshow Bob Roberts
plot: Sideshow Bob is released from prison and runs for Mayor of Springfield. When he wins the election, Bart and Lisa suspect foul play and are determined to expose Bob's corruption.

title: Treehouse of Horror V
plot: The family's job at Mr. Burns' country estate goes awry when Homer goes mad; Homer's attempt to repair a toaster results in inadvertent time travel; The school staff turn cannibalistic.

title: Bart's Girlfriend
plot: Bart falls for Reverend Lovejoy's daughter and is surprised when she becomes a bad influence on him.

title: Lisa on Ice
plot: Homer gives all his attention to Bart because he is the star of his hockey team, which makes Lisa jealous. But when a rival team discovers that she is an excellent goalie, Bart suddenly has a rival for Homer's attention.

title: Homer Badman
plot: After a series of misunderstandings, Homer is labeled a pervert, and must try to clear his name.

title: Grampa vs. Sexual Inadequacy
plot: Homer and Abe hit the road to sell Abe's miraculous aphrodisiac.

title: Fear of Flying
plot: Marge goes into therapy to cure her of her traumatizing fear of flying.

title: Homer the Great
plot: Homer becomes a member of a mysterious organization called the Stonecutters and is heralded as "the chosen one".

title: And Maggie Makes Three
plot: Homer recounts the story of Maggie's birth when the kids ask why there are no photos of her in the family album.

title: Bart's Comet
plot: Bart discovers a comet that is on a collision course with Springfield.

title: Homie the Clown
plot: Homer becomes a Krusty the Clown stand-in, but is mistaken for the real Krusty by the Springfield mafia.

title: Bart vs. Australia
plot: After he makes a collect call to Australia and refuses to pay for it, Bart sparks an international incident, with the Simpsons forced to travel to the country in order to repair political relations.

title: Homer vs. Patty and Selma
plot: Desperate for money, Homer takes a loan from Patty and Selma; Bart discovers a natural talent for ballet.

title: A Star Is Burns
plot: The citizens of Springfield decide to host their very own film festival and a popular movie critic from New York arrives to be a judge.

title: Lisa's Wedding
plot: A fortune teller gives Lisa a look at her wedding in the year 2010.

title: Two Dozen and One Greyhounds
plot: Santa's Little Helper's new mate has puppies, and Mr. Burns schemes to steal them and make them into a coat.

title: The PTA Disbands
plot: Marge fills in for Mrs. Krabappel during a teachers' strike.

title: 'Round Springfield
plot: When Bart is hospitalized, Lisa runs into her hero, Bleeding Gums Murphy, who is also a patient. However, when he dies soon after, she is devastated.

title: The Springfield Connection
plot: Marge deals with corruption and crime when she joins the Springfield police force.

title: Lemon of Troy
plot: When a group of Shelbyville kids steal Springfield's sacred lemon tree, Bart and his friends venture there to get the tree back.

title: Who Shot Mr. Burns? Part One
plot: After Mr. Burns steals oil from Springfield Elementary, an unknown person, seemingly in retaliation, shoots him.
episode_title: Who Shot Mr. Burns? Part One

title: Who Shot Mr. Burns? Part Two
plot: As Mr. Burns lies in intensive care, Chief Wiggum - with some help from Lisa - tries to find out who shot him.
episode_title: Who Shot Mr. Burns? Part Two

title: Radioactive Man
plot: Milhouse is cast as Radioactive Man's sidekick in a Hollywood production of the comic book.

title: Home Sweet Home-Dum-Diddly Doodily
plot: Marge and Homer lose custody of the kids, who are sent to live at the Flanders' house.

title: Bart Sells His Soul
plot: Bart casually sells his soul to Milhouse for five bucks but later regrets it. Moe converts his dank bar into a fun family restaurant.

title: Lisa the Vegetarian
plot: A trip to a local petting zoo convinces Lisa to give up meat, despite excessive pressure to convince her not to do so.

title: Treehouse of Horror VI
plot: A freak lightning storm causes giant advertising mascots to come to life; The children are terrorized by Groundskeeper Willie in their dreams; Homer finds himself trapped in another dimension.

title: King Size Homer
plot: Determined to avoid a work exercise program, Homer intentionally gains weight in order to qualify for disability and work from home. However, he soon realizes that being morbidly obese comes with its own problems.

title: Mother Simpson
plot: After faking his own death, Homer meets a woman in the cemetery who turns out to be his mother. While he is shocked by her reappearance as he was always told she was dead, she harbors a deep secret.

title: Sideshow Bob's Last Gleaming
plot: Sideshow Bob again escapes from prison and takes control of a TV screen at an air show, demanding all television stations immediately go off the air.

title: The Simpsons 138th Episode Spectacular!
plot: Troy McClure hosts a retrospective of the first 137 episodes of The Simpsons (1989).

title: Marge Be Not Proud
plot: Marge's relationship with Bart is strained when he is caught shoplifting before Christmas.

title: Team Homer
plot: Homer starts a bowling team with Moe, Apu and Otto, but when Mr. Burns discovers the team was funded with his money, he insists on joining. Meanwhile, Springfield Elementary introduces uniforms.

title: Two Bad Neighbors
plot: Former President George Bush and his wife, Barbara, move into the Simpsons' neighborhood and soon clash with Bart and Homer.

title: Scenes from the Class Struggle in Springfield
plot: After buying a Chanel suit at a bargain price, Marge finds herself invited to a country club by a former schoolmate. Taken in by the opulence of the place, she is soon overcome by a desperation to fit in.
episode_title: Scenes from the Class Struggle in Springfield

title: Bart the Fink
plot: Krusty is left almost broke after Bart inadvertently rats him out to the IRS, forcing him to take drastic action.

title: Lisa the Iconoclast
plot: Lisa may figure out what to do when she discovers that Springfield's founding father was actually a murderous thief while researching for an essay.

title: Homer the Smithers
plot: When Smithers is forced to take a vacation, he appoints Homer as his temporary replacement.

title: The Day the Violence Died
plot: Bart and Lisa meet a homeless person who claims to have created Itchy, one half of the cat and mouse team of their favorite cartoon series, "Itchy & Scratchy."

title: A Fish Called Selma
plot: Washed-up movie star Troy McClure starts dating Selma in an attempt to silence bizarre rumors about his personal life and resuscitate his career.

title: Bart on the Road
plot: Unable to get out of a mis-scheduled spring vacation, Principal Skinner makes up the holiday "Go to Work with Your Parents Day," giving Lisa the chance to spend time with Homer, and Bart the chance to work with Patty & Selma at the DMV. When Bart makes his own fake driver's license and Martin wins a bundle at the stock market, Bart rents a car, and takes Milhouse, Martin, and Nelson Muntz on a huge road trip.

title: 22 Short Films About Springfield
plot: A series of vignettes highlights a day in the life of various Springfield residents.

title: Raging Abe Simpson and His Grumbling Grandson in 'The Curse of the Flying Hellfish'
plot: Another member of Grampa Simpson's WWII platoon dies, leaving only him and Mr. Burns. Years earlier, the men stole a number of priceless masterpieces from Nazi Germany, and now Mr. Burns aims to ensure he is the one to inherit them.
episode_title: Raging Abe Simpson and His Grumbling Grandson in 'The Curse of the Flying Hellfish'

title: Much Apu About Nothing
plot: Anti-immigration fever sweeps Springfield, which threatens to lead to the deportation of Apu, until Homer decides to reject the mob mentality and help him become a legal citizen.

title: Homerpalooza
plot: Determined to prove he is still cool, Homer takes Bart and Lisa to the Hullabalooza music festival, where he finds he has a talent for being shot in the stomach, and joins the festival's freak show.

title: Summer of 4'2"
plot: After realizing how unpopular she is, a disillusioned Lisa sees the vacation to Ned Flanders' beach house as an opportunity to reinvent herself.

title: Treehouse of Horror VII
plot: Bart discovers his Siamese twin in the attic; Lisa becomes a God after she accidentally creates life in a science fair project; Kang and Kodos plot to conquer the planet.

title: You Only Move Twice
plot: After moving to another town to begin a new job, Homer must decide whether or not he should stay when the rest of the family have a hard time with the transfer.

title: The Homer They Fall
plot: Homer becomes a boxer after Moe discovers his amazing ability to take a punch.

title: Burns, Baby Burns
plot: The Simpsons try to reunite Homer's boss, Mr. Burns, with Larry, Burns' long-lost son.

title: Bart After Dark
plot: Marge leads a crusade against a local burlesque house after she discovers Bart working there.

title: A Milhouse Divided
plot: When Kirk and Luann hit a roadblock in their marriage, Luann announces that she is planning to get a divorce, causing Homer to worry about his own marriage.

title: Lisa's Date with Density
plot: At school, Nelson is caught with a cache of stolen items in his locker (including the "H" hood emblem from Supt. Chalmers' car) and is assigned to do chores with Groundskeeper Willie. Lisa is caught observing the goings-on and is assigned detention, where she develops a crush on Nelson. Lisa tries to reform Nelson, and it works for awhile. However, as the old saying goes, you can't teach a juvenile delinquent new tricks and it isn't long before Nelson is back to his old ways; he and his buddies had been caught throwing spoiled food at Skinner's house and tries to lie ...

title: Hurricane Neddy
plot: After a hurricane hits Springfield and destroys Ned Flanders' house, he suffers a breakdown and is forced to confront problems from his childhood.

title: The Mysterious Voyage of Homer
plot: At Springfield's annual chili cook-off, Homer eats a spicy concoction containing hallucinogenic peppers from Guatemala, and subsequently has a vision which makes him doubt Marge is his soul mate.

title: The Springfield Files
plot: Special Agents Mulder and Scully arrive in Springfield after Homer claims to have seen an alien.

title: The Twisted World of Marge Simpson
plot: Marge enters the pretzel vending business, but when she fails, Homer recruits some help from the mob.
episode_title: The Twisted World of Marge Simpson

title: Mountain of Madness
plot: Homer and Mr. Burns get trapped in a snowed-in cabin during a company retreat.

title: Simpsoncalifragilisticexpiala(Annoyed Grunt)cious
plot: Marge is stressed from motherhood and hired a British nanny to help out around the house, and to everyone at Rosie, she teaches Bart and Lisa how to behave.

title: The Itchy & Scratchy & Poochie Show
plot: Krusty becomes alarmed at the flagging ratings for "The Itchy & Scratchy Show" and demands it be corrected. The producers reason some new gimmicks are needed to inject fresh air and - after a focus group doesn't quite go as well as planned - decide to introduce a new character named Poochie, a rapping cartoon dog that is supposed to become friends with Itchy and Scratchy. Homer auditions to do Poochie's voice and wins the part. Poochie's first cartoon, "The Beagle Has Landed," premieres to great fanfare but is poorly received to say the least. The producers decide ...

title: Homer's Phobia
plot: After Marge befriends John, a gay store owner, Homer worries that his presence will have a negative effect on Bart's sexuality.

title: Brother from Another Series
plot: Grudge against his brother Side Show Bob, Cecil tries to kill Springfield with hydro-electric dam explosion which was fonded hollowed structure by him. Side Show Bob also has a good Side.

title: My Sister, My Sitter
plot: Bart is outraged when Lisa becomes his babysitter.

title: Homer vs. the 18th Amendment
plot: After Bart inadvertently becomes drunk at a St. Patrick's Day celebration, an old prohibition law banning drinking in Springfield is rediscovered and enforced. Desperate to keep alcohol in the city, Homer takes matters into his own hands.

title: Grade School Confidential
plot: Bart discovers Principal Skinner and Mrs Krabappel kissing, and it's not long before the whole town knows of their secret affair.

title: The Canine Mutiny
plot: After he fraudulently obtains a credit card, Bart buys a new dog named Laddie. When the items he purchased are repossessed, he lies that Santa's Little Helper is the dog he bought, and soon misses his pet.

title: The Old Man and the Lisa
plot: Burns loses his fortune and recruits Lisa to help him get it back.
episode_title: The Old Man and the Lisa

title: In Marge We Trust
plot: Marge becomes a church counselor; Homer discovers his face on a Japanese detergent logo.

title: Homer's Enemy
plot: Industrious Frank Grimes starts working at the plant and becomes irritated by Homer's laziness; Bart buys a run-down factory for a dollar.

title: The Simpsons Spin-Off Showcase
plot: Troy McClure introduces possible Simpsons spin-offs: "Chief Wiggins, P.I.," "The Love-Matic Grandpa," "The Simpson Family Smile-Time Variety Hour".

title: The Secret War of Lisa Simpson
plot: After a prank destroys half the town, Bart is shipped away to military school. Lisa, seeking a challenge, decides to enroll with him, but is faced with discrimination as the school's only girl cadet.
episode_title: The Secret War of Lisa Simpson

title: The City of New York vs. Homer Simpson
plot: Homer must travel to New York to get his car back, which is illegally parked at World Trade Center Plaza.
episode_title: The City of New York vs. Homer Simpson

title: The Principal and the Pauper
plot: At his 20th anniversary celebration as school principal, Principal Skinner is discovered to be an imposter of the real Seymour Skinner.

title: Lisa's Sax
plot: Homer recounts the story of Bart's first day of school, which corresponds with the story of how Lisa got her saxophone.

title: Treehouse of Horror VIII
plot: Homer battles mutants after Springfield is annihilated by a neutron bomb; Bart has his DNA mixed with a fly; Marge is revealed to be a witch in colonial Springfield.

title: The Cartridge Family
plot: After a massive soccer riot, Homer purchases a gun to protect the family.

title: Bart Star
plot: A damning report on childhood obesity in Springfield leads to the formation of a pee-wee football team. After belittling Ned Flanders, Homer ends up coaching the team, but his favoring of Bart makes him unpopular.

title: The Two Mrs. Nahasapeemapetilons
plot: Apu receives a letter from his mother stating that it's time for him fulfilled his arranged marriage obligation, he pretends Marge is his wife.

title: Lisa the Skeptic
plot: Another day at Springfield Elementary School, another field trip - this time to an archaeological dig. During the dig, Lisa unearths what appears to be a fossilized human skeleton with wings.

title: Realty Bites
plot: Marge becomes a real-estate agent.

title: Miracle on Evergreen Terrace
plot: When Bart accidentally burns down the family's Christmas tree and gifts, he claims that a robber stole everything. As a result, the town gets them a new tree and pitches in to raise funds.

title: All Singing, All Dancing
plot: Homer is disappointed when the western he rented turns out to be a musical, so the family reminds him of the musical moments in the show's history.

title: Bart Carny
plot: Bart and Homer befriend two carnies and invite them to stay with them, but the carnies soon swindle the Simpsons out of their house.

title: The Joy of Sect
plot: An evil cult called the Movementarians brainwashes the citizens of Springfield and it's up to Marge to get them back.

title: Das Bus
plot: While the kids become stranded on a desert island, Homer attempts to cash in on the Internet.

title: The Last Temptation of Krust
plot: After a disastrous performance, Krusty changes his image and becomes an edgy stand-up.

title: Dumbbell Indemnity
plot: Homer and Moe attempt insurance fraud so that Moe can support his new girlfriend. When Homer ends up in jail, Moe has to decide whether or not to come forward.

title: Lisa the Simpson
plot: Lisa fears she is losing her intelligence when she learns about the fabled Simpson gene. Meanwhile, Jasper freezes himself in the Kwik-E-Mart freezer.

title: This Little Wiggy
plot: Bart is reluctant to hang out with Ralph Wiggum, until he gains access to Chief Wiggum's master key to the city.

title: Simpson Tide
plot: Homer causes an international incident after he joins the Naval reserves.

title: The Trouble with Trillions
plot: Homer is forced to spy for the IRS after an audit. But when he is asked to retrieve a trillion dollar bill from Mr. Burns, he switches sides and the two flee to Cuba for refuge.

title: Girly Edition
plot: Bart and Lisa become locked in competition when they anchor a children's news program. Meanwhile, Homer adopts a helper monkey.

title: Trash of the Titans
plot: Homer becomes the sanitation commissioner for Springfield. His ineptitude pollutes the town and leads to a drastic solution.

title: King of the Hill
plot: After humiliating Bart at a church picnic, Homer resolves to get in shape. Soon, he is contacted by an energy bar company that wants him to climb a mountain as a promotion.

title: Lost Our Lisa
plot: Lisa gets lost after she tries to take a bus to a museum.

title: Natural Born Kissers
plot: Homer and Marge's attempt to spice up their marriage leads to the couple being chased naked through Springfield.

title: Lard of the Dance
plot: A new girl arrives at Springfield Elementary and becomes instantly popular, with Lisa forced to organize a dance at her school, while Homer and Bart try to start their own grease business.

title: The Wizard of Evergreen Terrace
plot: Homer's midlife crisis leads to a disastrous attempt at being an inventor.

title: Bart the Mother
plot: When Bart accidentally kills a mother bird, he tries to make amends by raising the eggs.

title: Treehouse of Horror IX
plot: Homer receives an evil hair transplant; Bart and Lisa get trapped in an Itchy and Scratchy cartoon; Maggie is revealed to be an alien.

title: When You Dish Upon a Star
plot: Homer becomes a Hollywood insider when he befriends Alec Baldwin and Kim Basinger.
episode_title: When You Dish Upon a Star

title: D'oh-in' in the Wind
plot: Homer becomes a hippie after a revelation about his middle name.

title: Lisa Gets an 'A'
plot: When Lisa cheats on a test, she has a moral crisis when her perfect score qualifies the school for grant money; Homer adopts a lobster as a pet.

title: Homer Simpson in: 'Kidney Trouble'
plot: Homer gets cold feet before a transplant operation which could save Grampa's life.

title: Mayored to the Mob
plot: Homer deals with corruption when he becomes Mayor Quimby's bodyguard.

title: Viva Ned Flanders
plot: When Homer takes Ned to Las Vegas in an attempt to get him to loosen up, the two end up drunkenly marrying a pair of cocktail waitresses.

title: Wild Barts Can't Be Broken
plot: The children of Springfield revolt after a curfew is enforced.

title: Sunday, Cruddy Sunday
plot: Homer and his friends head to the Superbowl, but are forced to sneak in when they discover their tickets are counterfeit.

title: Homer to the Max
plot: After a dimwitted TV character is coincidentally named Homer Simpson, Homer changes his name to Max Power.

title: I'm with Cupid
plot: The husbands of Springfield plot revenge after Apu outshines them on Valentine's Day.

title: Marge Simpson in 'Screaming Yellow Honkers'
plot: Marge's new SUV gives her a potent case of road rage.

title: Make Room for Lisa
plot: Lisa feels that her relationship with her father will never be close, and she develops stress-induced stomach pains; Marge inadvertently knocks out Milhouse.

title: Maximum Homerdrive
plot: Homer completes a cross country delivery for a trucker who dies before completing it, and takes Bart along for the ride. Meanwhile, Marge and Lisa experience problems with a novelty doorbell they purchase.

title: Simpsons Bible Stories
plot: Three famous religious stories are retold Simpsons style as the family nods off at church.

title: Mom and Pop Art
plot: Homer becomes the talk of the Springfield art community when a failed barbecue pit he worked on is mistaken for an art project.

title: The Old Man and the 'C' Student
plot: Bart is punished with community service at the Retirement Castle after he ruins Springfield's chances of hosting the Olympics.
episode_title: The Old Man and the 'C' Student

title: Monty Can't Buy Me Love
plot: When a wealthy man moves to Springfield, Mr. Burns begins to feel that he is losing his grasp on the citizens and decides to enlist the help of Homer.

title: They Saved Lisa's Brain
plot: Lisa is invited to join the Springfield chapter of MENSA and after Mayor Quimby flees, the group ends up running the city. Meanwhile, Homer poses for a series of erotic photos.

title: Thirty Minutes Over Tokyo
plot: The Simpsons must perform on a Japanese game show after Homer loses their money on a vacation.

title: Beyond Blunderdome
plot: Convinced he's the only man with guts to tell him the truth, Mel Gibson insists Homer accompanies him in Hollywood to help fix his newest film project.

title: Brother's Little Helper
plot: Bart is put on medication to control his behavior, but the pills cause him to become paranoid and insane.

title: Guess Who's Coming to Criticize Dinner?
plot: Homer's negative reviews as a food critic puts his life in danger. Fortunately he has Lisa fighting for him.
episode_title: Guess Who's Coming to Criticize Dinner?

title: Treehouse of Horror X
plot: The Simpsons attempt to cover up their accidental murder of Ned Flanders. Bart and Lisa acquire super powers. An electronic apocalypse threatens Springfield.

title: E-I-E-I-(Annoyed Grunt)
plot: Homer cowards out of a pistol-duel and hides out with the rest of the family on a country farm.

title: Hello Gutter, Hello Fadder
plot: Homer becomes a minor celebrity around Springfield after bowling a perfect game.

title: Eight Misbehavin'
plot: Apu struggles with fatherhood after Manjula gives birth to octuplets.

title: Take My Wife, Sleaze
plot: Homer's attempt at creating a motorcycle gang attracts a real gang, who kidnap Marge.

title: Grift of the Magi
plot: A toy company purchases Springfield Elementary and uses the student body as a focus group for their new Christmas toy Funzo.

title: Little Big Mom
plot: Lisa finds out how rough Marge has it when her mom is in traction and she becomes the woman of the house. Homer and Bart's antics get her so worked up she conspires to teach them a lesson.

title: Faith Off
plot: Bart is led to believe he has special healing powers after a tent revival.

title: The Mansion Family
plot: Homer receives responsibility for Mr. Burns' mansion when he is on leave and takes Burns' yacht to international waters to have a party.

title: Saddlesore Galactica
plot: The Simpsons get an abused horse and make him a contender in horse racing. Homer finds out a secret conspiracy about jockeys. Lisa tries to reach President Clinton when the results of a school band talent competition seem tainted.

title: Alone Again, Natura-Diddly
plot: Ned deals with his grief after Maude's untimely death.

title: Missionary: Impossible
plot: When Homer is wanted dead for reneging on a 10,000 dollar pledge to PBS, Reverend Lovejoy sets him up for missionary work in the South Pacific until the heat dies down.

title: Pygmoelian
plot: Plastic surgery not only transforms Moe the Bartender from ugly to hunky, it helps gets him a job on a hit daytime drama.

title: Bart to the Future
plot: Bart gets a glimpse of the future while the family is on vacation at an Indian casino.

title: Days of Wine and D'oh'ses
plot: Homer doesn't like it when Barney quits drinking; Bart and Lisa get into trouble when they enter a photo contest for the new phone book cover.

title: Kill the Alligator and Run
plot: Fearing he only has three years to live, Homer moves the family to Florida so he can live a better life, until they become wanted criminals after injuring a famous alligator.

title: Last Tap Dance in Springfield
plot: Lisa has difficulties learning to tap dance; Bart and Milhouse ditch summer camp to spend a week living in the mall.

title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad, Mad Marge
plot: Everybody loves the new Simpsons' house guest Becky. Except Marge, who thinks Becky wants to kill her.
episode_title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad, Mad Marge

title: Behind the Laughter
plot: Fans are invited to take a behind-the-scenes look at "The Simpsons," revisiting some of the most memorable experiences the family has been through.

title: Treehouse of Horror XI
plot: Homer must do one good deed to get into Heaven; Bart and Lisa encounter a witch in a gingerbread house; Super-intelligent dolphins strike back at humanity.

title: A Tale of Two Springfields
plot: Springfield is split in two when Homer revolts because his area code is changed; the new town walls itself off from the neighbors.

title: Insane Clown Poppy
plot: After he learns he has a daughter, Krusty turns to Homer for parenting advice.

title: Lisa the Treehugger
plot: Lisa's crush on an environmental activist inspires her to live in a tree threatened by loggers.

title: Homer vs. Dignity
plot: Desperate for money, Homer accepts payment from Mr. Burns in exchange for humiliating himself.

title: The Computer Wore Menace Shoes
plot: Homer's gossip website becomes a huge hit, but when his information runs out he resorts to making up news.

title: The Great Money Caper
plot: The whole town of Springfield conspires to teach Homer and Bart a lesson after the pair begin running confidence scams.

title: Skinner's Sense of Snow
plot: A freak blizzard traps the students of Springfield Elementary inside their school. Their lives at stake, they are at the mercy of the rescue efforts of a woozy Homer and Ned.

title: HOMR
plot: An x-ray reveals a crayon lodged in Homer's brain. After the crayon is removed, Homer experiences a sudden surge in intelligence, making him closer to Lisa and isolated from his friends.

title: Pokey Mom
plot: Marge befriends a convict with an artistic streak. Meanwhile, Homer battles the chiropractic industry after he creates a miracle back pain cure.

title: Worst Episode Ever
plot: Bart and Milhouse are left in charge of the comic book store after Comic Book Guy is hospitalized.

title: Tennis the Menace
plot: Homer installs a tennis court in the backyard, but his lousy playing creates a rift in the family.

title: Day of the Jackanapes
plot: Sideshow Bob returns with a plan to brainwash Bart and kill Krusty.

title: New Kids on the Blecch
plot: A music producer offers Bart and his friends a chance to participate in an up-and-coming boy band, but the boys are not so After after making a discovery.

title: Hungry Hungry Homer
plot: Homer is forced to go on a hunger strike by the Springfield Isotopes after uncovering a secret plan to have the baseball team moved to New Mexico.

title: Bye Bye Nerdy
plot: Problems with a bully lead Lisa to examine just what makes bullies aggressive. Meanwhile, Homer gets into the baby-proofing business.

title: Simpson Safari
plot: The Simpsons win a trip to Africa after Homer finds a golden animal cracker from the 60's in the loft.

title: Trilogy of Error
plot: Homer loses his thumb and must rush to the hospital for immediate surgery; Lisa tries to make it to the school with her project; Bart obtains illegal fireworks.

title: I'm Goin' to Praiseland
plot: With Homer's help, Flanders tries to establish a Christian theme park based on drawings in Maude's sketch book.

title: Children of a Lesser Clod
plot: After a debilitating injury forces him to stay indoors, Homer begins a daycare center.

title: Simpsons Tall Tales
plot: A hobo tells the Simpsons tall tales on a train ride to Delaware. In the first story, Homer is outcast from society as Paul Bunyan. Then, Lisa travels the country planting trees as Connie Appleseed. Finally, Bart and Nelson raft down the Mississippi as Tom Sawyer and Huck Finn.

title: Treehouse of Horror XII
plot: A gypsy puts a curse on Homer; The Simpsons' new automated house malfunctions and tries to kill Homer; Bart and Lisa attend a school for wizards.

title: The Parent Rap
plot: After Bart takes a joyride in a police car, a judge orders him to be tethered to Homer at all times.

title: Homer the Moe
plot: Homer and his friends are forced to drink in the Simpsons' garage after Moe the Bartender renovates his shady bar into a hipster hangout.

title: A Hunka Hunka Burns in Love
plot: Mr. Burns falls in love with a younger woman and recruits Homer to help him impress her.
episode_title: A Hunka Hunka Burns in Love

title: The Blunder Years
plot: A hypnotist uncovers a traumatic experience from Homer's childhood.

title: She of Little Faith
plot: Homer and Bart collaborate on a model rocket which destroys The First Church of Springfield. To raise money for repairs, the church sells advertising space, outraging Lisa - who becomes a Buddhist, with the help of guest star Richard Gere.

title: Brawl in the Family
plot: A social services officer brings unity to the Simpson family, but their newfound happiness is threatened when the cocktail waitress Homer married in Vegas shows up at their door.

title: Sweets and Sour Marge
plot: Marge rallies for a ban on sugar after Springfield is declared America's fattest city.

title: Jaws Wired Shut
plot: Marge can't deal with the quiet after Homer has his jaws wired shut.

title: Half-Decent Proposal
plot: Marge's high school sweetheart Artie Ziff returns and offers Homer a million dollars to spend a weekend with Marge.

title: The Bart Wants What It Wants
plot: Bart breaks up with his new girlfriend Greta, but gets jealous when she begins dating Milhouse.
episode_title: The Bart Wants What It Wants

title: The Lastest Gun in the West
plot: Bart meets a retired cowboy movie star and convinces him to make a comeback on The Krusty the Clown Show.
episode_title: The Lastest Gun in the West

title: The Old Man and the Key
plot: Abe gets his driver's license back to impress a new woman at the retirement home.
episode_title: The Old Man and the Key

title: Tales from the Public Domain
plot: Homer reads three stories from an overdue library book; with Homer as Odysseus trying to get home to Ithaca, Lisa as Joan of Arc leading the French to Victory and Bart as Hamlet avenging his father's death.

title: Blame It on Lisa
plot: Lisa sponsors an orphan in Brazil, and when he goes missing she convinces the family to go to Brazil to find him. While there, Homer is kidnapped.

title: Weekend at Burnsie's
plot: After a traumatizing eye injury, Homer becomes a habitual user of medical marijuana.

title: Gump Roast
plot: In this clip show, the citizens of Springfield honor Homer Simpsons with a Roast, but the festivities take a turn for the worst when aliens crash it.

title: I Am Furious Yellow
plot: Bart's comic about Homer becomes a hit on-line, prompting Homer to attempt to control his anger.

title: The Sweetest Apu
plot: Apu's marriage is on the rocks after Manjula finds out he cheated on her.

title: Little Girl in the Big Ten
plot: Lisa pretends to be a college student and loses favor with her classmates at Springfield Elementary in the process. A mysterious illness forces Bart to live in a plastic bubble.
episode_title: Little Girl in the Big Ten

title: The Frying Game
plot: Homer and Marge find themselves on death row after they are framed for murder.

title: Papa's Got a Brand New Badge
plot: Homer becomes chief of police after a scandal forces Wiggum out.
episode_title: Papa's Got a Brand New Badge

title: Treehouse of Horror XIII
plot: Homer clones himself with a magic hammock; Zombie cowboys come back from the dead after Springfield bans guns; The Simpsons family take a vacation on an island where Dr. Hibbert can turn people into animals.

title: How I Spent My Strummer Vacation
plot: When Marge, Lisa and Bart find out how hard Homer struggles to keep a roof over their heads, they enroll him in a Rock & Roll fantasy camp to relax at for a week.
episode_title: How I Spent My Strummer Vacation

title: Bart vs. Lisa vs. 3rd Grade
plot: Bart and Lisa are respectively held back and moved forward one grade, putting them in the same class.

title: Large Marge
plot: Marge accidentally gets breast implants.

title: Helter Shelter
plot: The Simpsons family must participate in a reality television show in which they try to live in the same way that the families did in the 1800s.

title: The Great Louse Detective
plot: Homer has to use Sideshow Bob in order to track down a potential assassin.

title: Special Edna
plot: After Skinner once again has let Mrs. Krabappel down, Bart takes her to the cinema. To cheer her up, Bart nominates Krabappel for the 'teacher of the year' award. The nominations is accepted, and soon the Simpsons family and Mrs. Krabappel are going to the award ceremony in Orlando, Florida, where Skinner tries to get back Krabappel by asking her to marry him.

title: The Dad Who Knew Too Little
plot: Homer hires a private detective to learn more about Lisa.
episode_title: The Dad Who Knew Too Little

title: The Strong Arms of the Ma
plot: Marge takes up body-building to boost her self-esteem after a mugging, but the family finds they just can't cope with a Marge that can bench-press 500 pounds.
episode_title: The Strong Arms of the Ma

title: Pray Anything
plot: Homer turns to religion to help him get what he wants, and is soon awarded the church in an injury settlement. Homer then turns the church into his personal party pad, and Reverend Lovejoy leaves Springfield to wallow in its hedonism.

title: Barting Over
plot: When Bart finds out Homer has used all the money Bart got for doing a commercial when he was a baby, he moves out of the house and into the same building as famous skateboarder, Tony Hawk, whose skateboarding tour Bart joins.

title: I'm Spelling as Fast as I Can
plot: Lisa participates in the Spellympics, but Homer is busy traveling cross-country as Krusty Burger test-markets a new sandwich. Lisa is confident that she will win, until she learns that the contest is rigged against her.
episode_title: I'm Spelling as Fast as I Can

title: A Star Is Born Again
plot: Ned Flanders starts dating a famous movie star, but has difficulties with the tabloids following them everywhere.

title: Mr. Spritz Goes to Washington
plot: The family makes Krusty run for Congress because of air traffic being redirected to fly dangerously close to their house.

title: C.E.D'oh
plot: Homer takes over the power plant after tricking Mr. Burns into making him the official owner of the power plant.

title: 'Scuse Me While I Miss the Sky
plot: Lisa becomes interested in astronomy and starts fighting the light pollution which is preventing her from being able to enjoy her new hobby.
episode_title: 'Scuse Me While I Miss the Sky

title: Three Gays of the Condo
plot: Finding an old note, Homer discovers Marge secretly hated him many years back. Upset, he leaves the house and moves in with two gays.

title: Dude, Where's My Ranch?
plot: Homer writes a Christmas carol called "Everybody Hates Ned Flanders," which soon becomes so popular that the family decides to leave town for a while.

title: Old Yeller-Belly
plot: Homer throws out Santa's Little Helper for not saving him from a fire, but soon the dog becomes Duff's new mascot.

title: Brake My Wife, Please
plot: Because of Homer losing his driver's license, Marge has to drive everyone everywhere, which is so stressful for her that she accidentally runs over Homer leading to the two seeing a marriage counselor.

title: The Bart of War
plot: Bart and Milhouse are forced into community service after destroying Flanders' memorial and join separate community groups, pitting themselves against each other.

title: Moe Baby Blues
plot: After saving Maggie's life, Moe develops a special bond with her, much to Homer's dismay.

title: Treehouse of Horror XIV
plot: First, Homer kills the Grim Reaper and takes his place in Reaper Madness. Then, Professor Frink's father is revived, only to kill people and steal their organs in Frinkenstein. Finally, Bart and Milhouse get a stop watch that can stop time in Stop the World, I Want To Goof Off.

title: My Mother the Carjacker
plot: Homer's mother returns to Springfield, and the city pardons her from the charges against her. Mr Burns is furious about this and makes a plan to get Mona Simpson in prison.

title: The President Wore Pearls
plot: Lisa feuds with Principal Skinner after being elected school president.

title: The Regina Monologues
plot: Prime minister Tony Blair welcomes the Simpsons to England where they run into author J.K. Rowling and actor Ian McKellen.

title: The Fat and the Furriest
plot: At the dump Homer is videotaped while being attacked by a bear. The town regards him a coward, so Homer decides to strike back at the bear.

title: Today, I Am a Clown
plot: Krusty decides to do what he never did when he was thirteen years old - have a Bar Mitzvah.

title: 'Tis the Fifteenth Season
plot: After spending all his money on an expensive gift for himself, and the family thinking he should be less of an egoist, Homer decides to change his ways.

title: Marge vs. Singles, Seniors, Childless Couples and Teens and Gays
plot: A concert for babies ends in a riot, so the childless adults of Springfield gather to make the town less child-friendly.
episode_title: Marge vs. Singles, Seniors, Childless Couples and Teens and Gays

title: I, (Annoyed Grunt)-Bot
plot: Homer pretends to be a robot and competes in Robot Wars to win Bart's affection; Lisa has cat trouble.

title: Diatribe of a Mad Housewife
plot: Marge is inspired to write a novel, but the storyline of the book (a fat, mean husband, and a handsome, sweet neighbor) makes Homer jealous.

title: Margical History Tour
plot: Marge tells Lisa, Bart and Millhouse three history stories because the library doesn't have any.

title: Milhouse Doesn't Live Here Anymore
plot: Milhouse moves to Capital City, and therefore Lisa and Bart become best friends.

title: Smart & Smarter
plot: When Maggie is revealed to have an IQ of 167, Lisa is no longer the genius of the family, causing a rivalry between the sisters.

title: The Ziff Who Came to Dinner
plot: Artie Ziff is discovered hiding out in the Simpsons' attic.
episode_title: The Ziff Who Came to Dinner

title: Co-Dependent's Day
plot: Marge takes up heavy drinking to spend more time with Homer. Bart and Lisa confront a famous movie director about the drop in quality his films have taken.

title: The Wandering Juvie
plot: After playing a prank on the whole town, Bart is sentenced to six months of juvenile detention. There he meets Gina, who forces Bart to escape with her.

title: My Big Fat Geek Wedding
plot: Mrs. Krabapel falls for Comic Book Guy and they plan a Star Trek like wedding. Principal Skinner plans to prevent it.

title: Catch 'Em If You Can
plot: Homer and Marge try to have a vacation without the kids but Bart and Lisa follow them everywhere they go.

title: Simple Simpson
plot: Homer becomes a costumed vigilante who uses pies for weapons after witnessing Lisa get humiliated at a competition at the state fair.

title: The Way We Weren't
plot: Marge and Homer find out that they actually kissed each other at age 10 without knowing they were each other's first kisses, and tell the story about this.

title: Bart-Mangled Banner
plot: An accidental photo showing Bart mooning the American flag makes the Simpsons the most hated family in town.

title: Fraudcast News
plot: After Mr. Burns is erroneously reported as dead, he buys all of he media outlets in order to prevent them from writing scathing articles about him.

title: Treehouse of Horror XV
plot: Ned gains the power to foresee people's deaths; Maggie is shrunk inside a vitamin capsule and swallowed; Eliza Simpson and her sidekick hunt down a murderer.

title: All's Fair in Oven War
plot: Homer buys Marge a new kitchen, and Marge likes cooking in the new kitchen so much she attends the Ovenfresh Bakeoff.

title: Sleeping with the Enemy
plot: Because she thinks her own children do not appreciate her anymore, Marge becomes a mother figure for Nelson.

title: She Used to Be My Girl
plot: Marge becomes jealous when Lisa begins idolizing her old high school friend, Chloe Talbot, a famous reporter.
episode_title: She Used to Be My Girl

title: Fat Man and Little Boy
plot: Bart begins designing T-shirt slogans, and his T-shirts become very popular among the citizens of Springfield.

title: Midnight Rx
plot: Homer goes to Canada with Apu and Ned to purchase Grampa's medication, but the three have problems getting home because the border guard thinks Apu is a terrorist.

title: Mommie Beerest
plot: Homer gives Moe an enormous amount of money so he doesn't have to close down.

title: Homer and Ned's Hail Mary Pass
plot: A video of Homer dancing becomes so popular that all major sports players hires Homer to design celebration dances for them.
episode_title: Homer and Ned's Hail Mary Pass

title: Pranksta Rap
plot: Bart went to a rap concert Marge told him not to go to. In order to avoid punishment from Marge, he makes Marge and Homer believe he has been kidnapped.

title: There's Something About Marrying
plot: A townsperson comes out of the closet when Springfield legalized same-sex marriages in a plot to bolsterwtourism; Homer uses the Internet to become a minister.

title: On a Clear Day I Can't See My Sister
plot: After bullying her, Bart is restricted by court order to come too close to Lisa.
episode_title: On a Clear Day I Can't See My Sister

title: Goo Goo Gai Pan
plot: Selma decides to adopt a child, so the whole family goes to China.

title: Mobile Homer
plot: After a garage-cleaning accident, Marge wants Homer to get life insurance. Instead, the family gets an RV.

title: The Seven-Beer Snitch
plot: Springfield builds an opera house, but since no-one attends it they convert it into a prison. Old and forgotten laws are used to fill the prison, and therefore Homer goes to jail for kicking a can five times in a row. In jail, Homer becomes a snitch

title: Future-Drama
plot: Bart and Lisa see into the future where their lives have changed.

title: Don't Fear the Roofer
plot: Homer meets a new friend, Ray the Roofer, but gets confined to a mental institution when his friends and family think he made him up.

title: The Heartbroke Kid
plot: Bart starts living on food from the new candy machine in school only, but he becomes so overweight that he has to go to a fat camp.

title: A Star Is Torn
plot: Lisa attends a singing competition for children, and Homer becomes her manager because of his skill to write songs that the crowd loves.

title: Thank God It's Doomsday
plot: Homer hears about the Rapture, and by using numerology to calculate when the Rapture is coming he learns that it is only one week away.

title: Home Away from Homer
plot: After Homer humiliates Ned Flanders, Ned, Rod, and Todd decides to leave Springfield and live in Humbleton, Pennsylvania.

title: The Father, the Son, and the Holy Guest Star
plot: Bart is expelled from Springfield Elementary, and Bart is therefore enrolled in St. Jerome's Catholic School.
episode_title: The Father, the Son, and the Holy Guest Star

title: The Bonfire of the Manatees
plot: When Marge leaves Homer because he allowed an adult movie being shot in their house, she seeks self fulfillment in protecting manatees.

title: The Girl Who Slept Too Little
plot: A new cemetery right outside the window of Lisa's room makes Lisa suffer from many sleepless nights.
episode_title: The Girl Who Slept Too Little

title: Milhouse of Sand and Fog
plot: Maggie contracts the chicken pox and Homer gets the great idea to charge parents to get their own children sick by throwing a pox party, but his plan backfires.

title: Treehouse of Horror XVI
plot: An android son replaces Bart; Homer and friends are the quarry in Mr. Burns' hunting tournament; a witch turns townsfolk into their Halloween costumes.

title: Marge's Son Poisoning
plot: Marge and Bart start spending more time together, and make a tradition of cycling to a tea house in a small village outside Springfield.

title: See Homer Run
plot: When a recall election puts Mayor Quimby's job up for grabs, Homer seizes the opportunity to win office and gain his daughter's love.

title: The Last of the Red Hat Mamas
plot: Milhouse tutors Lisa in Italian, and Marge joins the Cheery Red Tomatoes, a group that plans to rob Mr. Burns of one million dollars worth of Faberg eggs.
episode_title: The Last of the Red Hat Mamas

title: The Italian Bob
plot: The Simpsons become lost in Italy, finding their way to a small town that Sideshow Bob has become the mayor of.

title: Simpsons Christmas Stories
plot: Homer tells the tale of the first Christmas ever, while Grandpa pursues his decade-old feud with Santa.

title: Homer's Paternity Coot
plot: When a frozen mailman from the 60's is found in a Springfield glacier, doubts arise about whether Abe really is Homer's father.

title: We're on the Road to D'ohwhere
plot: When Homer is on his way to Vegas to meet up with his friends, he has to make a detour to take Bart to an education camp. Meanwhile, Marge has discovered a surprising source of income.
episode_title: We're on the Road to D'ohwhere

title: My Fair Laddy
plot: Bart and Lisa bets whether Lisa can turn Groundskeeper Willie into a proper gentleman.

title: The Seemingly Never-Ending Story
plot: In this story within a story within a story within a story, a cave-exploring expedition, an angry sheep and a lovestruck Moe become inextricably entwined.

title: Bart Has Two Mommies
plot: Marge starts babysitting the Flanders boys, leading Homer to spend more time with Bart and Lisa. Bart gets kidnapped by a lonely movie chimpanzee.

title: Homer Simpson, This Is Your Wife
plot: As part of a new Fox show, the Simpsons participate in a wife-swap.
episode_title: Homer Simpson, This Is Your Wife

title: Million Dollar Abie
plot: After blowing Springfield's chances for an NFL franchise, Grandpa goes to an assisted-suicide center, then becomes a bullfighter.

title: Kiss Kiss, Bang Bangalore
plot: Homer gets sent to India when the power plant is relocated there. Selma and Patty kidnap Richard Dean Anderson after he spurns their MacGyver fan club.

title: The Wettest Stories Ever Told
plot: While waiting for the dinner at the Frying Dutchman, the family starts telling three stories about ships: "Journey on the Mayflower", "Mutiny on the Bounty", and "The Neptune Adventure".

title: Girls Just Want to Have Sums
plot: Springfield Elementary is divided into two separate schools (one for boys, one for girls) following Principal Skinner's demotion. Concerned that the boys are receiving a higher standard of education, Lisa disguises herself as a boy.
episode_title: Girls Just Want to Have Sums

title: Regarding Margie
plot: After hitting her head on a stool Marge suffers from amnesia. Slowly but surely memories are starting to come back, except memories about Homer.

title: The Monkey Suit
plot: After seeing a museum exhibit on evolution, in which creation is labeled a myth, an outraged Ned Flanders teams with Reverend Lovejoy to blackmail Principal Skinner into requiring creationism to be taught in classrooms, eventually at the expense of any mention of evolution. Lisa becomes outraged herself, and forms a student organization to teach evolution, leading to a creationism vs. evolution trail, a la Inherit the Wind.

title: Homer and Marge Turn a Couple Play
plot: Marge and Homer try their luck at celebrity marriage counselling.
episode_title: Homer and Marge Turn a Couple Play

title: The Mook, the Chef, the Wife and Her Homer
plot: When Fat Tony has to take a time-out due to a whacking attempt, Homer and Bart take over the business.
episode_title: The Mook, the Chef, the Wife and Her Homer

title: Jazzy & The Pussycats
plot: Lisa becomes depressed when Bart becomes a better jazz musician than her. So she decides to set up an animal shelter in the Simpsons' attic.

title: Please Homer, Don't Hammer 'Em
plot: Marge begins her own carpentry business, but Homer becomes the face of the business because nobody will take a female carpenter seriously. And Bart uses Principal Skinner's peanut allergy to his advantage.

title: Treehouse of Horror XVII
plot: A meteorite turns Homer into a rampaging blob with a voracious appetite; Bart brings a Golem to life; an alien invasion hoax turns real.

title: G.I. (Annoyed Grunt)
plot: Homer is duped into signing up for the Army, and his hijinks after basic training ultimately results in a military occupation of Springfield.

title: Moe'N'a Lisa
plot: Lisa helps Moe become a distinguished poet, but she turns on him when he takes all the credit for his newfound greatness.

title: Ice Cream of Margie: With the Light Blue Hair
plot: Homer becomes an ice cream man after being fired from the plant, and Marge uses his leftover Popsicle sticks to create folk art figures.
episode_title: Ice Cream of Margie: With the Light Blue Hair

title: The Haw-Hawed Couple
plot: Bart and Nelson become best friends, but Bart surprisingly discovers that the fringe benefits aren't worth Nelson's neediness.

title: Kill Gil, Vol. 1 & 2
plot: The Simpsons let Gil stay with them during Christmas. However, he stays for 11 months because Marge can't tell him "no."

title: The Wife Aquatic
plot: Homer returns Marge to Barnacle Bay, where she spent her beloved summer vacations. But when they get there, they discover that it is no longer a tourist spot.

title: Revenge Is a Dish Best Served Three Times
plot: While Homer tries to get revenge on a driver who cut him off, his family warns him of the folly of revenge by telling stories based on "The Count of Monte Cristo," "Revenge of the Nerds," and "Batman."
episode_title: Revenge Is a Dish Best Served Three Times

title: Little Big Girl
plot: When Bart performs a heroic act, Springfield grants him 1 wish. Barts asks for a driver's license, and he drives to a nearby town. There, he meets a teen (Natalie Portman) who thinks he is 16, and the two begin dating.

title: Springfield Up
plot: A parody of the "Up Series" of British documentaries, in which a filmmaker follows Homer and his friends from grade school into their 40s.

title: Yokel Chords
plot: In this parody of The Sound of Music (1965), Lisa becomes a tutor for Cletus' seven children, until Krusty tries to exploit them as entertainers. Meanwhile, Bart becomes emotionally attached to his school-appointed psychiatrist.

title: Rome-old and Juli-eh
plot: Selma and Grampa fall in love and end up getting married, a marriage both Homer and Patty are against.

title: Homerazzi
plot: Homer becomes a successful Paparazzi, but Springfield's celebrities decide to get their revenge on him.

title: Marge Gamer
plot: Marge decides to find out what there Internet has to offer and soon gets hooked on an online role-playing game; Homer referees Lisa's soccer game.

title: The Boys of Bummer
plot: Bart becomes the most hated person in Springfield after he is the goat in a championship baseball game, and Homer new job as a mattress salesman ruins his and Marge's sex life.

title: Crook and Ladder
plot: Homer, Moe, Apu and Principal Skinner become volunteer firefighters. But just because they're not getting paid doesn't mean that they can't find a way to receive compensation.

title: Stop or My Dog Will Shoot
plot: Homer unwittingly drags the family into a cornfield maze after attempting to leave a boring Harvest fest that Marge brought them to. When everyone except Homer escapes, Santa's Little Helper rescues him and becomes the town hero. So the Simpsons enroll him in Police Dog Academy where he's teamed with Lou.
episode_title: Stop or My Dog Will Shoot

title: 24 Minutes
plot: Bart and Lisa join forces to stop the school bullies from setting off a stink bomb at the school bake sale.

title: You Kent Always Say What You Want
plot: After Kent Brockman is fired as a news anchor, he and Lisa use the Internet to expose the Fox News Conspiracy.
episode_title: You Kent Always Say What You Want

title: He Loves to Fly and He D'ohs
plot: Homer falls in love with private planes after taking a flight to Chicago with Mr. Burns. So Marge hires Homer a "life manager" to help him think positively and find a job that will allow him to fly for a living.
episode_title: He Loves to Fly and He D'ohs

title: Homer of Seville
plot: Homer becomes an opera star after an injury improves his singing voice. His newfound popularity forces him to hire a personal assistant, who turns out to be an obsessed stalker.

title: Midnight Towboy
plot: Homer becomes the most hated man in town after he becomes a tow truck driver, and Marge teaches Maggie to not be an over-dependent baby.

title: I Don't Wanna Know Why the Caged Bird Sings
plot: Marge promises to visit a convicted bank robber in prison, but is afraid to follow through. But when the convict escapes from prison, Marge is the first person he pays a visit to.
episode_title: I Don't Wanna Know Why the Caged Bird Sings

title: Treehouse of Horror XVIII
plot: The eighteenth Simpsons Halloween Special features parodies of the movies "E.T." and "Mr. and Mrs. Smith."

title: Little Orphan Millie
plot: Milhouse's parents are lost at sea, which causes him to become a troubled loner. But his new persona makes him the new most popular kid at school, which sparks jealousy in Bart.

title: Husbands and Knives
plot: When Marge becomes a successful businesswoman, Homer becomes worried that she will dump him for a trophy husband. Therefore, he decides to have plastic surgery to make himself look like a hunk.

title: Funeral for a Fiend
plot: Bart is responsible for Sideshow Bob's death after his latest attempt at revenge is foiled, but is his death actually part of the plan?

title: Eternal Moonshine of the Simpson Mind
plot: Homer goes to Dr. Frink to help him recover his memories from the night before, and he discovers, based on his interpretation of the memories, that Marge is having an affair.
episode_title: Eternal Moonshine of the Simpson Mind

title: E Pluribus Wiggum
plot: Springfield becomes the site of the first presidential primary. The townspeople soon get sick of all of the presidential candidates sucking up to them, and decide to support their own write-in candidate: Ralph Wiggum.

title: That '90s Show
plot: Homer and Marge tell the kids about their life in the early 1990s before they were born, when Marge was enrolled in Springfield College and Homer was the lead singer of a grunge rock band

title: Love, Springfieldian Style
plot: A series of romantic Valentine's Day parodies based on "Bonnie and Clyde," "Lady and the Tramp," and "Sid and Nancy."

title: The DeBarted
plot: The new prankster in Bart's fourth grade class actually turns out to be a mole brought in by Principal Skinner to infiltrate Bart's inner circle. Homer falls in love with his loaner car after Marge wrecks their old one.

title: Dial 'N' for Nerder
plot: One of Bart's pranks results in Martin's death, but Lisa doesn't want him to confess because she would be considered an accomplice. Marge hires a television crew to find out if Homer is cheating on his diet.

title: Smoke on the Daughter
plot: Marge has Lisa take up ballet, mainly to have Lisa live out her own childhood dreams. Lisa then succumbs to peer pressure from her ballet mates and takes up smoking. Meanwhile, Homer and Bart try to start their own beef jerky business.

title: Papa Don't Leech
plot: When the Simpsons discover that Lurleen Lumpkin is on the skids, Marge reluctantly agrees to take her in and help her find her deadbeat dad who abandoned her 30 years ago.

title: Apocalypse Cow
plot: Bart tries to save the cow he raised for his 4-H club from the slaughterhouse, and in the process winds up getting accidentally engaged to one of Cletus's daughters.

title: Any Given Sundance
plot: Lisa's documentary about her family is accepted into the Sundance Film Festival. However, her family gets upset with her when they discover that the film is far from flattering.

title: Mona Leaves-a
plot: Homer's mom dies, and as part of her will, she asks him to spread her ashes. However, her request turns out to be part of her final act of rebellion against the system.

title: All About Lisa
plot: In a parody of "All About Eve," Lisa stabs Krusty in the back, takes his job, and wins a prestigious award. Meanwhile, Homer and Bart take up coin collecting.

title: Sex, Pies and Idiot Scrapes
plot: Homer and Ned go into business together as bounty hunters, and Marge takes a job at an erotic bakery.

title: Lost Verizon
plot: Bart gets in trouble with Marge after she finds out that he has Denis Leary's cell phone and is using it to make prank phone calls.

title: Double, Double, Boy in Trouble
plot: Bart trades lives with his multi-millionaire lookalike, but discovers that his lookalike's life isn't all he thought it would be.

title: Treehouse of Horror XIX
plot: The Simpsons' 19th Halloween Special, with parodies of "Transformers," "Mad Men," and "It's the Great Pumpkin, Charlie Brown."

title: Dangerous Curves
plot: The Simpsons take a Fourth of July vacation to a cabin hotel, which cause Homer and Marge to reminisce about two episodes from their past where they stayed in the cabin.

title: Homer and Lisa Exchange Cross Words
plot: Homer gets a job breaking up couples, and Lisa becomes an expert crossword puzzle solver, but Homer bets against her in a competition.
episode_title: Homer and Lisa Exchange Cross Words

title: MyPods and Boomsticks
plot: Homer suspects that the family of Bart's new Muslim friend from Jordan is part of a terrorist plot, and Lisa becomes obsessed with her new MyPod.

title: The Burns and the Bees
plot: Mr. Burns wins a professional basketball team in a poker game, and the new arena he plans to have Springfield build for the team threatens to interfere with Lisa's new bee sanctuary.

title: Lisa the Drama Queen
plot: Lisa and her new best friend create their own fantasy world, but Marge doesn't want Lisa to see her friend anymore after she finds out that they're too far gone in it.

title: Take My Life, Please
plot: Homer finds out that he actually won the senior class president election, and he gets an opportunity to find out how his life would have been different if it had happened.

title: How the Test Was Won
plot: Bart and his fellow underachievers are taken on a "field trip" to Capital City so that they can miss the standardized test, and Homer makes sure that nothing bad happens until their insurance goes back into effect.

title: No Loan Again, Naturally
plot: The Simpsons lose their house, but Flanders buys it and offers to rent it back to them. But when they turn out to be less-than-reliable renters, Flanders kicks them out.

title: Gone Maggie Gone
plot: In order to rescue Maggie from a Catholic orphanage, Lisa must solve a series of puzzles to reveal the identity of a gem that will bring peace to Springfield.

title: In the Name of the Grandfather
plot: The Simpsons take Grandpa to Ireland so he can go back to visit a pub he went to during the war, but Grandpa and Homer get suckered into buying the bar.
episode_title: In the Name of the Grandfather

title: Wedding for Disaster
plot: Homer is kidnapped moments before he and Marge are supposed to re-renew their vows. However, Marge comes to the conclusion that Homer left her at the altar.

title: Eeny Teeny Maya Moe
